rules.ruleString: Must be enrolled in course version {4504, M20022}
(Must have passed an (I/W) unit in {SWK1011} and  Must have passed an (I/W) unit in {ATS1359, ATS1840} and  Must have passed 48 (I/W) credit points at levels {1})

unitName: Social welfare and practice with communities
description: The unit intends to help students develop knowledge and insight into the everyday activities of community work and the theoretical assumptions that underpin community work and how these relate, in particular, to the child welfare and aged care contexts.
faculty: Faculty of Medicine, Nursing and Health Sciences
